## Editor Layout

The main editor should target `LiveAnnotationSession`.

Use a vertical layout with four sections.

### 1. Fixture Header

Shows the selected fixture and readonly context:

```text
Session: [ title ]
Fixture: [ fixture dropdown ]

Home: SK Brann      Away: Bodo/Glimt
Venue: Brann Stadion
Date: 2026-03-29
```

Implementation notes:

- the `fixture` reference should use a dropdown-like reference editor
- once selected, team and venue cells should read from the referenced `Fixture`
- if no fixture is selected, show a placeholder message:
  - `Select a fixture to begin annotation`

### 2. Event Widget Row

This is the main action strip:

```text
[ Goal ] [ Card ] [ Foul ] [ Offside ] [ Substitution ] [ Period ]
```

Each widget creates a child in `events` and immediately moves the caret into the new event form.

Implementation notes:

- use transformation menu actions or intention-style actions
- each button should append the corresponding event concept
- the new event should be initialized with:
  - `minute = 0`
  - `second = 0`
  - `team = fixture.homeTeam` as a temporary default

### 3. Active Event Form

When the caret is inside an event, show an expanded form-style editor for that event.

Base event fields first:

```text
Minute: [ minute ]
Team: [ dropdown ]
```

Then event-specific fields.

#### GoalEvent

```text
Minute: [ minute ]
Team: [ dropdown ]
Scorer: [ player dropdown ]
Assist: [ player dropdown ]
```

#### CardEvent

```text
Minute: [ minute ]
Team: [ dropdown ]
Player: [ player dropdown ]
Card: [ Yellow | Red | Second Yellow ]
```

#### FoulEvent

```text
Minute: [ minute ]
Team: [ dropdown ]
Offender: [ player dropdown ]
Fouled player: [ player dropdown ]
```

#### OffsideEvent

```text
Minute: [ minute ]
Team: [ dropdown ]
Player: [ player dropdown ]
```

#### SubstitutionEvent

```text
Minute: [ minute ]
Team: [ dropdown ]
Player out: [ player dropdown ]
Player in: [ player dropdown ]
```

#### PeriodEvent

```text
Minute: [ minute ]
Team: [ dropdown ]
Period: [ FIRST_HALF_START | FIRST_HALF_END | SECOND_HALF_START | SECOND_HALF_END | ... ]
```

### 4. Timeline

The bottom section is the event list for the whole session.

Compact row style:

```text
00:00  BRN  Period         FIRST_HALF_START
12:14  BRN  Card           Jacob Lungi Sorensen  Yellow
27:58  BRN  Goal           Felix Horn Myhre      assist Bard Finne
37:34  BOD  Substitution   Hakon Evjen -> Jostein Gundersen
```

Implementation notes:

- start with a simple vertical collection
- later this can be upgraded to MPS Extensions `tables`

## Scoping Rules

The editor UX depends on filtered reference scopes.

### Fixture scope

`LiveAnnotationSession.fixture` should resolve only to `Fixture` roots visible in the model or imported models.

### Team scope

For every `Event.team`, only allow:

- `session.fixture.homeTeam`
- `session.fixture.awayTeam`

### Player scope

For `Event.player`, only allow players from `Event.team`.

### Goal assist scope

For `GoalEvent.assistBy`, only allow players from `GoalEvent.team`.

### Foul victim scope

For `FoulEvent.fouledPlayer`, prefer players from the opposite team.

For the MVP, if opposite-team scoping is awkward, allow all players from both fixture teams and refine later.

### Substitution scope

For:

- `SubstitutionEvent.playerOut`
- `SubstitutionEvent.playerIn`

only allow players from `SubstitutionEvent.team`.

## Editor Components

To keep the editor maintainable, define reusable editor components for:

- `FixtureSummary`
- `EventTimeFields`
- `EventTeamField`
- `PlayerReferenceField`
- `TimelineRow`

That gives each event editor a small amount of custom logic instead of duplicating the same cells.

